♪ As you're by my side ♪

12
00:02:22,800 --> 00:02:24,730
breakfast with you every morning.

13
00:02:25,610 --> 00:02:32,280
♪ Never thought I'd turn back
and see us tied by a red string ♪

14
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:40,230
♪ The weight of family,
my hand in yours ♪

15
00:02:41,230 --> 00:02:45,130
♪ Destiny ends in companionship ♪

16
00:02:45,390 --> 00:02:48,800
♪ With my wish fulfilled at last ♪

17
00:02:49,290 --> 00:02:54,990
♪ Now I always have someone to long for ♪

18
00:02:56,970 --> 00:03:02,150
♪ Even rooftops remember
each moonlit night ♪

19
00:03:25,420 --> 00:03:29,060
♪ I see the clarity in your eyes ♪

20
00:03:29,410 --> 00:03:32,340
♪ Asking for the guidance of my life ♪

21
00:03:32,900 --> 00:03:35,930
♪ Who caught our fleeting moment? ♪

22
00:03:36,740 --> 00:03:39,890
♪ A stunning glimpse from the past ♪

23
00:03:40,079 --> 00:03:40,920
Sir,

24
00:03:41,200 --> 00:03:42,840
since what happened to Marquis of Jing'an,

25
00:03:42,840 --> 00:03:44,079
outside Prince of Dingbei's Mansion,

26
00:03:44,079 --> 00:03:45,200
there have been people from Haiyou Sect

27
00:03:45,200 --> 00:03:46,329
secretly watching.

28
00:03:47,200 --> 00:03:48,320
It's been days.

29
00:03:49,079 --> 00:03:50,540
Should we eliminate them?

30
00:03:52,640 --> 00:03:53,640
How many?

31
00:03:53,640 --> 00:03:54,520
Two.

32
00:03:55,800 --> 00:03:57,460
Chancellor Su is suspicious.

33
00:03:58,320 --> 00:04:00,680
The more clearly they see,

34
00:04:02,080 --> 00:04:03,610
the more convinced he'll be

35
00:04:03,800 --> 00:04:07,040
that there's nothing suspicious
about Father-in-law's death.

36
00:04:07,040 --> 00:04:07,920
Have Zhuifeng and Zhuiyu

37
00:04:07,920 --> 00:04:09,800
continue to secretly protect Tan.

38
00:04:09,800 --> 00:04:11,080
Don't alert them.

39
00:04:11,800 --> 00:04:12,560
Yes.

40
00:04:18,200 --> 00:04:20,860
You can't bear
to see Her Highness heartbroken,

41
00:04:20,959 --> 00:04:22,820
so you can only endure in silence.

42
00:04:23,680 --> 00:04:25,200
But now that it's over,

43
00:04:26,900 --> 00:04:29,200
why don't you tell her the truth?

44
00:04:30,070 --> 00:04:30,930
Telling her now

45
00:04:32,520 --> 00:04:34,520
might relieve her pain for a moment.

46
00:04:36,080 --> 00:04:37,680
But should this plan go awry,

47
00:04:38,680 --> 00:04:41,140
it could lead to irreparable consequences.

48
00:04:41,520 --> 00:04:42,440
So we can only let Her Highness

49
00:04:42,440 --> 00:04:43,760
continue to misunderstand you?

50
00:04:42,880 --> 00:04:49,170
♪ Looking back, what a long road filled with uncertainties ♪

51
00:04:44,520 --> 00:04:45,780
What Chancellor Su did

52
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:47,000
clearly shows

53
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:49,400
he still harbors doubts about this matter.

54
00:04:50,080 --> 00:04:50,760
I can't

55
00:04:50,490 --> 00:04:56,640
♪ Who to share
the wavering candle light with? ♪

56
00:04:50,760 --> 00:04:52,120
risk Tan's life.

57
00:04:58,800 --> 00:05:01,660
♪ Words are cold ♪

58
00:05:02,540 --> 00:05:05,130
♪ I always remember the promise
to get old with you ♪

59
00:05:05,730 --> 00:05:10,520
♪ Sigh! Vows are like snowflakes
resting on my palm ♪

60
00:05:11,520 --> 00:05:15,690
♪ The vicissitudes of life never cease ♪

61
00:05:15,800 --> 00:05:16,960
Tan,

62
00:05:16,390 --> 00:05:19,810
♪ You and I are looking for the truth ♪

63
00:05:19,440 --> 00:05:21,000
I haven't done well enough.

64
00:05:19,970 --> 00:05:25,340
♪ Injured though we were,
we still sought the right direction ♪

65
00:05:23,200 --> 00:05:25,330
I failed to fulfill the promise I made—

66
00:05:27,340 --> 00:05:30,840
♪ Time has melted ice ♪

67
00:05:27,440 --> 00:05:28,900
to protect the Ming family

68
00:05:31,080 --> 00:05:32,200
and to keep you free from worry.

69
00:05:31,570 --> 00:05:35,659
♪ What is our original aspiration? ♪

70
00:05:36,620 --> 00:05:41,560
♪ We share the same thought and path ♪

71
00:05:44,060 --> 00:05:50,550
♪ Hope to pick flowers with you ♪

72
00:05:53,680 --> 00:05:54,880
During the days at the Court of Review,

73
00:05:54,880 --> 00:05:56,200
Chancellor, you've suffered.

74
00:05:56,200 --> 00:05:57,730
Rest assured, Chancellor.

75
00:05:57,880 --> 00:05:59,640
After the Minister of Justice
learned about this matter,

76
00:05:59,640 --> 00:06:01,320
he started an investigation personally.

77
00:06:01,320 --> 00:06:02,440
Since the Court of Review

78
00:06:02,440 --> 00:06:04,520
closed the case with the conclusion
that the prisoner took his own life,

79
00:06:04,520 --> 00:06:06,880
there should be no further complications.

80
00:06:06,880 --> 00:06:10,560
Prince of Dingbei lured me into his trap.

81
00:06:11,120 --> 00:06:13,050
How could he not have a backup plan?

82
00:06:14,240 --> 00:06:15,200
These days,

83
00:06:15,880 --> 00:06:18,320
has there been anything unusual
at Prince of Dingbei's Mansion?

84
00:06:18,320 --> 00:06:19,320
Since that night,

85
00:06:19,360 --> 00:06:20,330
people from Haiyou Sect

86
00:06:20,330 --> 00:06:22,120
have been closely watching
Prince of Dingbei's Mansion.

87
00:06:22,120 --> 00:06:24,120
Nothing unusual has been observed.

88
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:27,130
But that's precisely what puzzles me.

89
00:06:27,200 --> 00:06:28,960
Given Prince of Dingbei's methods,

90
00:06:28,960 --> 00:06:30,760
he would never resort to mere trickery.

91
00:06:30,760 --> 00:06:32,640
If his goal was to frame you

92
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:34,520
with such a crude means,

93
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:37,200
that's like disturbing the grass
only to startle the snake.

94
00:06:37,200 --> 00:06:38,560
An act that gains him nothing, right?

95
00:06:38,560 --> 00:06:39,870
Are you suggesting

96
00:06:40,640 --> 00:06:41,640
this trap

97
00:06:42,640 --> 00:06:45,000
was never meant to convict me

98
00:06:45,520 --> 00:06:47,320
of poisoning?

99
00:06:48,200 --> 00:06:51,120
Then what was his true purpose?

100
00:06:57,320 --> 00:06:58,520
Steamed buns for sale!

101
00:06:58,520 --> 00:07:00,720
Big, fragrant, and sweet steamed buns!

102
00:07:02,200 --> 00:07:03,330
Miss, how about two?

103
00:07:03,440 --> 00:07:04,440
Try my steamed buns.

104
00:07:04,440 --> 00:07:06,360
A time-honored brand, honest and fair.

105
00:07:06,360 --> 00:07:06,880
We use

106
00:07:06,880 --> 00:07:08,200
only the finest wheat flour.

107
00:07:08,200 --> 00:07:09,200
Two coins each.

108
00:07:09,320 --> 00:07:10,520
Miss, don't go!

109
00:07:11,440 --> 00:07:13,200
Miss, how about a bowl of noodles?

110
00:07:13,200 --> 00:07:14,320
The broth is rich.

111
00:07:14,320 --> 00:07:15,240
The noodles are chewy.

112
00:07:15,240 --> 00:07:16,000
The shredded chicken inside

113
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:17,400
is tender and delicious.

114
00:07:57,880 --> 00:07:59,280
Why are you following me?

115
00:08:00,680 --> 00:08:01,800
I apologize

116
00:08:01,880 --> 00:08:02,940
for offending you.

117
00:08:04,320 --> 00:08:06,000
You almost fell into the water,

118
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:07,120
so I helped you.

119
00:08:07,120 --> 00:08:08,450
How was that an offense?

120
00:08:09,680 --> 00:08:10,680
You're right.

121
00:08:11,200 --> 00:08:13,760
Thank you for saving me.

122
00:08:15,440 --> 00:08:17,000
Then can you tell me

123
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:18,650
why you've been following me

124
00:08:18,680 --> 00:08:20,680
all the way from East Market Street?

125
00:08:21,080 --> 00:08:22,210
You misunderstood.

126
00:08:22,320 --> 00:08:24,000
I happened to see you just now

127
00:08:24,120 --> 00:08:25,880
and thought we are acquainted,

128
00:08:26,080 --> 00:08:27,280
so I should greet you.

129
00:08:27,600 --> 00:08:28,320
But I couldn't find

130
00:08:28,320 --> 00:08:29,780
the right moment to speak.

131
00:08:30,080 --> 00:08:31,940
So I followed you all the way here.

132
00:08:32,039 --> 00:08:33,799
How are we acquainted?

133
00:08:34,679 --> 00:08:35,740
At the relief hall,

134
00:08:36,559 --> 00:08:38,440
when you handed out roast chicken
to the children,

135
00:08:38,440 --> 00:08:39,880
I was there too.

136
00:08:39,960 --> 00:08:41,620
We even exchanged a few words.

137
00:08:44,039 --> 00:08:45,320
Well, you've greeted me.

138
00:08:45,320 --> 00:08:46,200
You can leave.

139
00:08:54,480 --> 00:08:56,210
Roast chicken. Roast chicken.

140
00:09:01,440 --> 00:09:02,320
Hot and fresh daily.

141
00:09:02,320 --> 00:09:04,200
You've wandered
both East and West Markets today.

142
00:09:04,200 --> 00:09:05,600
What are you looking for?

143
00:09:06,040 --> 00:09:07,300
Something delicious.

144
00:09:07,680 --> 00:09:09,280
What kind of delicious food?

145
00:09:09,320 --> 00:09:10,440
Sweet? Glutinous?

146
00:09:10,600 --> 00:09:11,960
Light? Strong-flavored?

147
00:09:11,960 --> 00:09:14,290
Perhaps I can make a few recommendations.

148
00:09:14,320 --> 00:09:15,560
Her Highness doesn't like strong flavors.

149
00:09:15,560 --> 00:09:17,280
She prefers sweet and glutinous things.

150
00:09:17,280 --> 00:09:19,280
But lately, her appetite hasn't been good.

151
00:09:19,280 --> 00:09:21,680
Some soup or porridge might be better.

152
00:09:22,440 --> 00:09:24,710
You're buying food for Her Highness?

153
00:09:25,680 --> 00:09:26,800
Her Highness lost her father.

154
00:09:26,800 --> 00:09:27,680
She's heartbroken.

155
00:09:27,680 --> 00:09:29,480
She hasn't eaten for three days.

156
00:09:31,440 --> 00:09:32,810
What happened to the Ming family

157
00:09:32,810 --> 00:09:34,460
has chilled many hearts.

158
00:09:35,480 --> 00:09:37,320
His Lordship risked his life for Xian,

159
00:09:37,320 --> 00:09:39,440
only to meet such an end.

160
00:09:40,320 --> 00:09:42,440
Sir, come and try my meat buns.

161
00:09:42,600 --> 00:09:44,960
Do you have a way to help the Ming family?

162
00:09:49,840 --> 00:09:52,100
I'd better continue searching for food.

163
00:09:52,600 --> 00:09:53,430
Using delicious food

164
00:09:53,430 --> 00:09:54,450
to heal a broken heart

165
00:09:54,450 --> 00:09:55,410
is not baseless.

166
00:09:55,440 --> 00:09:57,200
Every plant and every taste

167
00:09:57,200 --> 00:09:58,080
in this world

168
00:09:58,480 --> 00:09:59,440
hold their own charm.

169
00:09:59,440 --> 00:10:01,010
As they say, everything is lovable,

170
00:10:01,010 --> 00:10:02,080
and everything has a soul.

171
00:10:02,080 --> 00:10:03,790
The warmth of daily life comforts

172
00:10:03,790 --> 00:10:04,840
people's hearts the most.

173
00:10:04,840 --> 00:10:06,300
That's exactly the basis.

174
00:10:10,560 --> 00:10:12,670
Why are you looking at me?

175
00:10:13,040 --> 00:10:14,230
You always use

176
00:10:14,260 --> 00:10:15,590
such flowery language?

177
00:10:17,680 --> 00:10:18,510
What I meant is

178
00:10:18,530 --> 00:10:20,790
tasty food can indeed soothe our hearts.

179
00:10:21,280 --> 00:10:22,250
Then tell me,

180
00:10:22,320 --> 00:10:23,480
what kinds of food

181
00:10:23,480 --> 00:10:24,540
can soothe hearts?

182
00:10:28,080 --> 00:10:28,800
Over there.

183
00:10:28,800 --> 00:10:29,800
Youchang's pancakes.

184
00:10:29,800 --> 00:10:30,960
Crispy, fragrant, and sweet.

185
00:10:30,960 --> 00:10:32,000
And on the east side of the bridge,

186
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:33,080
there's a dumpling shop—

187
00:10:33,080 --> 00:10:34,070
quite famous.

188
00:10:34,400 --> 00:10:36,480
Their dumplings are thin-skinned
and full of filling,

189
00:10:36,480 --> 00:10:37,560
with rich broth.

190
00:10:37,560 --> 00:10:38,080
And...

191
00:10:38,080 --> 00:10:38,660
Enough.

192
00:10:39,480 --> 00:10:41,340
Mr. Flowery, please lead the way.

193
00:10:42,840 --> 00:10:43,680
Sure, please.

194
00:10:55,200 --> 00:10:56,060
Your Highness,

195
00:10:56,560 --> 00:10:58,160
have a bite at least.

196
00:10:58,960 --> 00:11:00,040
If you continue like this,

197
00:11:00,040 --> 00:11:01,300
eating nothing at all—

198
00:11:01,440 --> 00:11:02,980
how can your body take it?

199
00:11:04,560 --> 00:11:05,280
Yeah.

200
00:11:05,840 --> 00:11:06,600
Yun Yi

201
00:11:06,600 --> 00:11:07,720
waited in line

202
00:11:07,750 --> 00:11:09,040
to buy these for you specially.

203
00:11:09,040 --> 00:11:10,770
She doesn't know what you like,

204
00:11:10,800 --> 00:11:13,130
so she bought one of everything she could.

205
00:11:14,850 --> 00:11:17,110
Sorry for making you worried these days.

206
00:11:17,200 --> 00:11:18,160
I'm fine.

207
00:11:18,920 --> 00:11:21,440
I just don't have much appetite.

208
00:11:27,920 --> 00:11:29,320
I'm sure Uncle

209
00:11:29,440 --> 00:11:31,370
wouldn't want to see you like this.

210
00:11:31,840 --> 00:11:32,960
If you feel sad,

211
00:11:32,960 --> 00:11:34,560
just cry freely.

212
00:11:34,600 --> 00:11:35,600
Or if you want to go somewhere,

213
00:11:35,600 --> 00:11:36,440
see someone,

214
00:11:36,500 --> 00:11:37,160
or do something,

215
00:11:37,160 --> 00:11:38,280
we'll go with you.

216
00:11:38,560 --> 00:11:40,020
But you can't swallow

217
00:11:40,040 --> 00:11:41,310
all your grief alone.

218
00:11:41,440 --> 00:11:42,370
If this continues,

219
00:11:42,370 --> 00:11:43,770
it will make you fall ill.

220
00:11:44,040 --> 00:11:45,150
I'm so worried.

221
00:11:52,480 --> 00:11:53,340
Your Highness,

222
00:11:54,080 --> 00:11:55,840
I've never told you this.

223
00:11:56,960 --> 00:12:00,800
Since I could remember things,

224
00:12:00,800 --> 00:12:01,930
I've been an orphan.

225
00:12:03,080 --> 00:12:04,880
I didn't know who my parents were

226
00:12:05,080 --> 00:12:07,290
or what a home was like.

227
00:12:07,600 --> 00:12:08,690
And I didn't know

228
00:12:08,960 --> 00:12:10,560
where I truly belonged.

229
00:12:11,680 --> 00:12:12,620
In those years,

230
00:12:13,320 --> 00:12:14,960
I wandered from place to place,

231
00:12:14,960 --> 00:12:16,420
with no place to call home.

232
00:12:17,040 --> 00:12:18,840
What I remember most vividly is

233
00:12:19,960 --> 00:12:22,020
I had no one to rely on when it was cold.

234
00:12:22,600 --> 00:12:23,800
And when I was hungry,

235
00:12:24,600 --> 00:12:25,960
I had no food to eat.

236
00:12:29,320 --> 00:12:32,850
At that time, I really thought

237
00:12:33,750 --> 00:12:35,800
the world was just that cold.

238
00:12:37,680 --> 00:12:39,740
But after joining the Jinyun Guards,

239
00:12:40,070 --> 00:12:41,790
I realized something.

240
00:12:43,680 --> 00:12:46,910
There must be warmth

241
00:12:46,930 --> 00:12:48,320
and light in this world.

242
00:12:49,320 --> 00:12:51,320
As long as you have faith,

243
00:12:52,200 --> 00:12:54,400
hardship and pain will disappear.

244
00:12:56,480 --> 00:12:57,780
We understand

245
00:12:57,880 --> 00:13:01,140
♪ A quiet wish born in the dark ♪

246
00:12:58,160 --> 00:12:59,820
that the light in your heart

247
00:13:00,440 --> 00:13:02,020
has been extinguished for now.

248
00:13:02,020 --> 00:13:05,260
♪ Will it reach someone's ears at all? ♪

249
00:13:03,840 --> 00:13:06,560
But we'll be right here with you

250
00:13:05,990 --> 00:13:09,680
♪ A fleeting brush in a passing glance ♪

251
00:13:07,200 --> 00:13:08,680
to get through this

252
00:13:09,440 --> 00:13:10,360
until

253
00:13:10,720 --> 00:13:13,780
♪ Etching longing deep within ♪

254
00:13:11,840 --> 00:13:13,200
that light in your heart

255
00:13:14,200 --> 00:13:15,320
shines again.

256
00:13:14,870 --> 00:13:18,270
♪ You are the flame ♪

257
00:13:18,920 --> 00:13:22,470
♪ That lights my endless night ♪

258
00:13:20,680 --> 00:13:21,800
Yun Yi is right.

259
00:13:22,320 --> 00:13:24,560
Tan, I don't have much else,

260
00:13:22,830 --> 00:13:27,980
♪ Because of the resolve
we see in each other's eyes ♪

261
00:13:24,960 --> 00:13:26,760
but I have a lot of warmth to give.

262
00:13:26,960 --> 00:13:29,160
Tan, for the rest of my life,

263
00:13:29,320 --> 00:13:32,480
I will warm you and protect you.

264
00:13:30,020 --> 00:13:33,060
♪ We believe in forever ♪

265
00:13:35,170 --> 00:13:39,230
♪ May the fleeting years
gather into points of light ♪

266
00:13:39,520 --> 00:13:42,860
♪ Hold on to this bond year after year ♪

267
00:13:43,200 --> 00:13:47,080
♪ Side by side through endless tales ♪

268
00:13:47,630 --> 00:13:51,320
♪ Love rests deep in heart and eyes ♪

269
00:13:48,960 --> 00:13:49,960
Thank you.

270
00:13:51,670 --> 00:13:55,350
♪ May the fleeting years gather into light,
and you are that point of light ♪

271
00:13:55,740 --> 00:13:59,110
♪ Time flows in silence,
through lingering nights ♪

272
00:13:59,850 --> 00:14:03,940
♪ Like stars in the long night ♪

273
00:14:04,350 --> 00:14:07,610
♪ Through all the changes, near or far ♪

274
00:14:06,160 --> 00:14:07,090
It's delicious.

275
00:14:08,100 --> 00:14:14,150
♪ I'll be with you
to enjoy the unfinished story ♪

276
00:14:29,800 --> 00:14:32,340
[Two months later]

277
00:14:34,200 --> 00:14:36,900
[Wentao Pavilion]

278
00:14:44,800 --> 00:14:46,080
Were these portraits...

279
00:14:46,080 --> 00:14:47,560
really prepared for me?

280
00:14:47,560 --> 00:14:48,840
You're not young anymore.

281
00:14:48,840 --> 00:14:50,840
It's time someone takes care of you.

282
00:14:55,080 --> 00:14:56,020
Wait,

283
00:14:56,200 --> 00:14:58,080
were they specially prepared for you

284
00:14:58,080 --> 00:14:59,320
because Chancellor Shu

285
00:14:59,320 --> 00:15:01,380
wanted to arrange a marriage for you?

286
00:15:04,480 --> 00:15:06,080
I have no such intentions.

287
00:15:06,320 --> 00:15:07,440
Since the portraits have been prepared,

288
00:15:07,440 --> 00:15:09,100
we might as well make use of it.

289
00:15:09,960 --> 00:15:11,680
Just pick a lady

290
00:15:11,710 --> 00:15:13,040
you truly like,

291
00:15:13,040 --> 00:15:14,650
and go meet her on my behalf.

292
00:15:14,960 --> 00:15:16,280
You're Commander Lu,

293
00:15:16,280 --> 00:15:17,200
bold and brave.

294
00:15:17,680 --> 00:15:19,740
You will surely win the lady's heart.

295
00:15:26,320 --> 00:15:27,960
I invited you two here

296
00:15:27,960 --> 00:15:29,690
to discuss important matters.

297
00:15:31,960 --> 00:15:33,020
This is important.

298
00:15:33,920 --> 00:15:36,080
Your wife's matter is important,

299
00:15:36,080 --> 00:15:37,090
but my marriage

300
00:15:37,110 --> 00:15:38,110
is not important?

301
00:15:43,600 --> 00:15:44,680
I've got an idea.

302
00:15:45,420 --> 00:15:48,080
Winning her heart
comes down to three key moves.

303
00:15:48,080 --> 00:15:50,800
First, cook for her.

304
00:15:50,840 --> 00:15:53,800
Second, help raise the children.

305
00:15:55,220 --> 00:15:57,380
Well said. You've outshone me.

306
00:15:57,420 --> 00:15:59,360
But Xu, you are not much of a cook,

307
00:15:59,440 --> 00:16:01,080
and you and she have no children.

308
00:16:01,080 --> 00:16:02,960
You can only cater to her pleasure

309
00:16:02,960 --> 00:16:04,040
and never give up.

310
00:16:04,920 --> 00:16:06,860
How to cater to her pleasure?

311
00:16:07,440 --> 00:16:08,740
That means

312
00:16:08,800 --> 00:16:10,960
everything Her Highness likes...

313
00:16:10,960 --> 00:16:12,840
You must like them too.

314
00:16:12,840 --> 00:16:14,720
Everything Her Highness wants to do...

315
00:16:14,720 --> 00:16:16,320
You do it with her.

316
00:16:16,320 --> 00:16:18,440
As the saying goes: stand by
your friends through thick and thin.

317
00:16:18,440 --> 00:16:20,320
So do whatever it takes
for your beloved wife.

318
00:16:20,320 --> 00:16:21,080
In short...

319
00:16:21,080 --> 00:16:21,960
Be willing

320
00:16:21,960 --> 00:16:23,320
to do everything for Her Highness.

321
00:16:23,320 --> 00:16:25,050
-That's right.
-That's right.

322
00:17:17,980 --> 00:17:20,910
Your Highness,
it doesn't look like you're pruning.

323
00:17:21,349 --> 00:17:22,950
More like cutting the roots.

324
00:17:32,240 --> 00:17:34,480
It's better to be harsh
than to let things slide.

325
00:17:34,480 --> 00:17:36,340
Perhaps I've grown too used to it.

326
00:17:43,680 --> 00:17:45,360
Your Highness, you even cut

327
00:17:45,360 --> 00:17:46,280
the new buds.

328
00:17:47,360 --> 00:17:49,480
It's quite ruthless.

329
00:17:51,360 --> 00:17:53,640
I... don't believe I can't do it.

330
00:17:55,840 --> 00:17:56,700
Your Highness!

331
00:17:56,960 --> 00:17:58,360
Why don't you let me do it?

332
00:18:02,480 --> 00:18:04,340
Why is tending flowers and plants

333
00:18:04,440 --> 00:18:06,770
harder than fighting on the battlefield?

334
00:18:06,920 --> 00:18:08,440
What isn't right to begin with—

335
00:18:08,440 --> 00:18:11,770
no matter how much effort
you force into it, it's all in vain.

336
00:18:23,240 --> 00:18:24,710
Catering to her pleasure?

337
00:18:24,880 --> 00:18:25,960
What a bad idea.

338
00:18:29,960 --> 00:18:31,680
All this money is for me?

339
00:18:32,480 --> 00:18:33,680
Cousin, I know you

340
00:18:33,960 --> 00:18:35,490
asked Tan out to shop today.

341
00:18:38,360 --> 00:18:39,360
Whatever Tan wants to eat

342
00:18:39,360 --> 00:18:40,280
or buy,

343
00:18:40,280 --> 00:18:41,360
just take her.

344
00:18:42,280 --> 00:18:43,880
Right now, only you, Cousin,

345
00:18:43,960 --> 00:18:45,360
can make Tan happy.

346
00:18:46,160 --> 00:18:48,680
Please do your best.

347
00:18:50,200 --> 00:18:51,200
Are you still

348
00:18:51,200 --> 00:18:52,460
the Jiang Qizhi I know?

349
00:18:53,040 --> 00:18:54,360
Since you called me Cousin,

350
00:18:54,360 --> 00:18:55,450
I'll surely find a way

351
00:18:55,450 --> 00:18:56,780
to make Tan happy today.

352
00:18:59,360 --> 00:19:00,880
Don't let Tan know about this.

353
00:19:00,590 --> 00:19:02,670
[Elegant Songs and Dances]

354
00:19:01,000 --> 00:19:01,680
Let's go.

355
00:19:02,040 --> 00:19:03,700
Don't worry, Cousin-in-law.

356
00:19:07,160 --> 00:19:08,040
Come here!

357
00:19:10,960 --> 00:19:11,760
Tan.

358
00:19:11,210 --> 00:19:12,510
[Elegant Songs and Dances]

359
00:19:13,280 --> 00:19:14,440
Whatever you want to eat

360
00:19:14,440 --> 00:19:15,160
or buy today,

361
00:19:15,160 --> 00:19:16,160
it's all on me.

362
00:19:16,680 --> 00:19:18,240
You've only been
the acting manager for a few days,

363
00:19:18,240 --> 00:19:20,240
and you're already being so generous.

364
00:19:20,240 --> 00:19:21,760
I guess Wentao Pavilion's business

365
00:19:21,760 --> 00:19:22,880
must be booming.

366
00:19:26,040 --> 00:19:29,560
Your Highness,
I want to buy a roast chicken.

367
00:19:29,920 --> 00:19:32,420
But can I charge it to the public account?

368
00:19:32,680 --> 00:19:33,600
My monthly allowance

369
00:19:33,600 --> 00:19:34,680
is nearly gone.

370
00:19:35,360 --> 00:19:37,830
You eat in the mansion every day.

371
00:19:38,120 --> 00:19:39,720
You have few daily expenses.

372
00:19:40,200 --> 00:19:42,000
What did you spend your money on?

373
00:19:44,760 --> 00:19:46,160
I bought roast chickens.

374
00:19:48,280 --> 00:19:49,880
I bought osmanthus sugar cakes

375
00:19:49,880 --> 00:19:51,120
for you yesterday.

376
00:19:51,520 --> 00:19:52,730
Where are they?

377
00:19:55,480 --> 00:19:56,520
I ate them.

378
00:19:57,760 --> 00:20:00,960
No osmanthus sugar cakes, no money.

379
00:20:00,980 --> 00:20:01,960
Today...

380
00:20:02,040 --> 00:20:03,430
Today, I'll surely buy you

381
00:20:03,430 --> 00:20:05,630
another pack of osmanthus sugar cakes.

382
00:20:06,200 --> 00:20:07,360
I was just joking.

383
00:20:07,440 --> 00:20:09,520
Just charge it to the public account.

384
00:20:09,580 --> 00:20:10,950
Thank you, Your Highness.

385
00:20:10,950 --> 00:20:11,960
No need for that.

386
00:20:11,960 --> 00:20:12,960
Today, everything is on me.

387
00:20:12,960 --> 00:20:13,820
Take the money.

388
00:20:15,200 --> 00:20:16,280
Thank you, Minmin.

389
00:20:16,680 --> 00:20:18,140
I'm leaving then.

390
00:20:30,070 --> 00:20:31,880
Minmin, you're so generous.

391
00:20:32,760 --> 00:20:34,760
The rest is yours to spend. Let's go.

392
00:20:37,040 --> 00:20:39,440
It's a day off today,
and you have nothing to do.

393
00:20:39,440 --> 00:20:41,500
Come with me to the Capital Garrison.

394
00:20:42,040 --> 00:20:44,170
There are a few reports from the north.

395
00:20:44,480 --> 00:20:45,920
Before presenting them to the court,

396
00:20:45,920 --> 00:20:47,320
we still need to discuss.

397
00:20:58,000 --> 00:20:58,920
Not today.

398
00:20:58,960 --> 00:21:01,000
I have other things to do today.

399
00:21:01,000 --> 00:21:01,730
Another day.

400
00:21:02,360 --> 00:21:02,960
Well...

401
00:21:03,480 --> 00:21:04,040
Jing...

402
00:21:05,400 --> 00:21:06,200
Jingran!

403
00:21:08,160 --> 00:21:09,440
Here you go. Take care.

404
00:21:10,680 --> 00:21:11,360
Okay.

405
00:21:13,640 --> 00:21:14,550
Here you go.

406
00:21:15,040 --> 00:21:15,880
Thank you.

407
00:21:17,200 --> 00:21:18,200
Miss Chicken Leg.

408
00:21:20,960 --> 00:21:22,190
Mr. Flowery?

409
00:21:22,680 --> 00:21:23,480
Miss Chicken Leg,

410
00:21:23,480 --> 00:21:24,810
you remember me at last.

411
00:21:26,160 --> 00:21:27,230
All sold out today!

412
00:21:27,360 --> 00:21:29,420
If you want some, come back tomorrow!

413
00:21:30,060 --> 00:21:31,210
Sold out already?

414
00:21:33,210 --> 00:21:34,540
Mr. Flowery,

415
00:21:34,920 --> 00:21:36,520
you like roast chickens too?

416
00:21:38,650 --> 00:21:39,750
I came here because of its reputation.

417
00:21:39,750 --> 00:21:40,880
But unfortunately,

418
00:21:40,880 --> 00:21:43,010
I'm not fated to try the roast chicken.

419
00:21:44,840 --> 00:21:46,550
He's so strange.

420
00:21:46,640 --> 00:21:48,970
He talked about fate with a roast chicken?

421
00:22:01,880 --> 00:22:02,880
Are you really giving it to me?

422
00:22:02,880 --> 00:22:04,160
Because last time,

423
00:22:04,160 --> 00:22:04,760
you took me to buy

424
00:22:04,760 --> 00:22:06,050
those delicious food.

425
00:22:06,680 --> 00:22:08,040
I can't give you any more.

426
00:22:08,040 --> 00:22:09,700
I only have one roast chicken.

427
00:22:11,000 --> 00:22:12,600
Thank you, Miss Chicken Leg.

428
00:22:18,200 --> 00:22:19,330
Eat.

429
00:22:19,440 --> 00:22:20,960
Eat it while it's hot.

430
00:22:20,960 --> 00:22:22,290
It tastes best that way.

431
00:22:23,000 --> 00:22:23,590
Okay.

432
00:22:28,200 --> 00:22:30,260
Tender, juicy, and not greasy at all.

433
00:22:30,400 --> 00:22:32,130
It's definitely worth trying.

434
00:22:32,680 --> 00:22:34,960
This shop's roast chicken is indeed good.

435
00:22:34,960 --> 00:22:35,950
But

436
00:22:36,400 --> 00:22:38,200
what His Highness makes

437
00:22:38,200 --> 00:22:39,060
is much better.

438
00:22:41,680 --> 00:22:43,030
His... His Highness?

439
00:22:45,680 --> 00:22:47,410
Xu made a roast chicken for you?

440
00:22:51,960 --> 00:22:52,900
May I

441
00:22:53,120 --> 00:22:54,480
know your name?

442
00:22:54,480 --> 00:22:55,690
My name is Yun Yi.

443
00:22:56,000 --> 00:22:57,600
I'm a concubine
in Prince of Dingbei's Mansion.

444
00:22:57,600 --> 00:22:59,480
Con... Concubine?

445
00:23:01,200 --> 00:23:01,660
This...

446
00:23:02,920 --> 00:23:05,000
I need to buy some osmanthus sugar cakes.

447
00:23:05,000 --> 00:23:06,060
I'm leaving first.

448
00:23:10,360 --> 00:23:12,680
They only sell fifty
roast chickens per day.

449
00:23:12,680 --> 00:23:15,210
If you want to eat it,
you'd better come early.

450
00:23:23,330 --> 00:23:26,370
When did Xu take a concubine?

451
00:23:39,480 --> 00:23:41,390
Tan, I found a merchant

452
00:23:41,410 --> 00:23:42,270
selling particularly exquisite jewelry

453
00:23:42,270 --> 00:23:43,760
a few days.

454
00:23:43,760 --> 00:23:46,290
You'll definitely like it.
It's right there.

455
00:23:51,200 --> 00:23:52,000
Ladies,

456
00:23:52,200 --> 00:23:54,860
take a look and
see if anything catches your eye.

457
00:23:58,440 --> 00:23:59,900
The design of this hairpin

458
00:23:59,930 --> 00:24:01,000
is indeed unique.

459
00:24:01,360 --> 00:24:03,160
I suppose it's quite expensive.

460
00:24:03,200 --> 00:24:04,840
You ladies are elegant.

461
00:24:04,920 --> 00:24:06,720
You two have exceptional taste.

462
00:24:06,880 --> 00:24:09,010
This hairpin is of the finest quality.

463
00:24:09,200 --> 00:24:11,400
The gems on it are of excellent quality.

464
00:24:11,400 --> 00:24:12,480
If you wear it,

465
00:24:12,520 --> 00:24:15,850
you'd surely look like
a fairy descending from the heavens.

466
00:24:15,960 --> 00:24:17,530
The totem on it

467
00:24:17,560 --> 00:24:18,960
looks quite unique as well.

468
00:24:18,960 --> 00:24:21,390
It doesn't seem to be from Xian.

469
00:24:22,440 --> 00:24:23,570
May I ask

470
00:24:24,200 --> 00:24:26,130
where does this jewelry come from?

471
00:24:27,960 --> 00:24:29,620
How can I reveal that?

472
00:24:30,040 --> 00:24:31,250
If everyone knew

473
00:24:31,280 --> 00:24:32,440
the source of my goods,

474
00:24:32,440 --> 00:24:33,890
how could I make a profit?

475
00:24:45,360 --> 00:24:47,150
I suppose these jewelry

476
00:24:47,200 --> 00:24:48,800
were all transported by sea, weren't they?

477
00:24:48,800 --> 00:24:50,280
I can see they have

478
00:24:50,300 --> 00:24:52,360
clear signs of saltwater corrosion.

479
00:24:52,680 --> 00:24:54,440
They can't be sold for
a high price like this.

480
00:24:54,440 --> 00:24:55,440
To be honest,

481
00:24:55,880 --> 00:24:56,850
these goods

482
00:24:56,890 --> 00:24:58,710
did indeed come by sea.

483
00:24:58,920 --> 00:25:00,440
That's what makes them
even more extraordinary.

484
00:25:00,440 --> 00:25:01,350
Here in Xian,

485
00:25:01,380 --> 00:25:02,910
they are truly one of a kind.

486
00:25:02,920 --> 00:25:04,580
If you ladies like any of them,

487
00:25:04,680 --> 00:25:06,000
I won't charge a high price.

488
00:25:06,000 --> 00:25:07,680
Consider it as making a friend.

489
00:25:07,680 --> 00:25:08,780
In the future, when I have good items,

490
00:25:08,780 --> 00:25:10,380
I'll save them for you first.

491
00:25:11,170 --> 00:25:12,680
Then I'll take all of these.

492
00:25:12,680 --> 00:25:14,030
What? Are you serious?

493
00:25:14,120 --> 00:25:15,960
If you get new designs in the future,

494
00:25:15,960 --> 00:25:17,360
you must save them for me first.

495
00:25:17,360 --> 00:25:19,960
Miss, you're truly
a straightforward person.

496
00:25:20,680 --> 00:25:21,760
Boss Minmin,

497
00:25:21,760 --> 00:25:22,810
Buy.

498
00:25:24,760 --> 00:25:26,480
Wearing these jewelry pieces out

499
00:25:26,480 --> 00:25:27,810
is indeed presentable.

500
00:25:28,440 --> 00:25:29,850
However, your stall

501
00:25:29,880 --> 00:25:31,410
might not be here every day.

502
00:25:31,880 --> 00:25:33,600
How will I find you in the future?

503
00:25:33,600 --> 00:25:34,500
I live in

504
00:25:34,530 --> 00:25:35,880
the Datong Inn on the street.

505
00:25:35,880 --> 00:25:36,880
My surname is Zhu.

506
00:25:36,920 --> 00:25:39,850
I'll be setting up my stall here
for the next few days.

507
00:25:46,680 --> 00:25:48,440
Tan, your taste is truly excellent.

508
00:25:48,440 --> 00:25:49,260
You were just asking about

509
00:25:49,260 --> 00:25:50,440
where the merchant lives.

510
00:25:50,440 --> 00:25:52,680
Are you planning to establish
a long-term partnership with him?

511
00:25:52,680 --> 00:25:53,920
These kinds of accessories

512
00:25:53,920 --> 00:25:54,920
won't take long to

513
00:25:54,930 --> 00:25:56,360
become popular in the capital.

514
00:25:56,360 --> 00:25:57,570
The business of Cuojin Pavilion

515
00:25:57,570 --> 00:25:59,300
will surely reach new heights.

516
00:25:59,840 --> 00:26:00,960
If that happens,

517
00:26:01,240 --> 00:26:03,500
Cuojin Pavilion will shut down for good.

518
00:26:03,960 --> 00:26:06,960
The prince's mansion will suffer
the consequences as well.

519
00:26:06,960 --> 00:26:07,960
Why is that?

520
00:26:09,160 --> 00:26:10,760
The patterns on these pieces

521
00:26:11,200 --> 00:26:12,400
and the designs

522
00:26:12,520 --> 00:26:14,180
are definitely not from Xian.

523
00:26:14,360 --> 00:26:16,240
I suspect they were smuggled in.

524
00:26:18,360 --> 00:26:20,680
So you were deliberately asking

525
00:26:20,680 --> 00:26:21,680
about that person's residence earlier.

526
00:26:21,680 --> 00:26:23,090
You learned he's staying at an inn

527
00:26:23,090 --> 00:26:24,680
and doesn't plan to settle down.

528
00:26:24,680 --> 00:26:25,880
It seems he intends to

529
00:26:26,280 --> 00:26:27,500
finish this batch of business

530
00:26:27,500 --> 00:26:28,960
and then move on to another place.

531
00:26:28,960 --> 00:26:29,870
Then these items

532
00:26:29,870 --> 00:26:31,010
must be illegal.

533
00:26:33,360 --> 00:26:34,360
Father's case

534
00:26:34,610 --> 00:26:35,680
was because it involved

535
00:26:35,680 --> 00:26:36,610
smuggled goods.

536
00:26:37,200 --> 00:26:38,040
That led the court

537
00:26:38,040 --> 00:26:39,500
to convict him of treason.

538
00:26:40,040 --> 00:26:42,400
Since these goods have already
made their way to the capital,

539
00:26:42,400 --> 00:26:44,330
it shows this isn't the first time.

540
00:26:44,360 --> 00:26:46,760
I suspect someone's
making a profit off this,

541
00:26:46,760 --> 00:26:47,960
and framing my father

542
00:26:48,440 --> 00:26:49,960
for smuggling.

543
00:26:51,880 --> 00:26:53,050
But even so,

544
00:26:53,480 --> 00:26:54,560
it doesn't prove

545
00:26:54,580 --> 00:26:56,710
that Uncle has nothing to do with this.

546
00:26:58,200 --> 00:27:00,450
These items all came by sea,

547
00:27:01,200 --> 00:27:02,440
and the only route for maritime trade

548
00:27:02,440 --> 00:27:03,990
in Xian was through

549
00:27:05,360 --> 00:27:06,070
Lingzhou.

550
00:27:19,960 --> 00:27:20,680
Your Highness.

551
00:27:20,680 --> 00:27:22,030
Two deserters from Yangxi Prefecture

552
00:27:22,030 --> 00:27:23,230
have come to meet you.

553
00:27:23,960 --> 00:27:27,280
They claim to be former subordinates
of the Marquis of Jing'an.

554
00:27:27,280 --> 00:27:28,080
Bring them in.

555
00:27:29,000 --> 00:27:29,800
Bring them in!

556
00:27:36,360 --> 00:27:38,100
Greetings, Your Highness.

557
00:27:39,120 --> 00:27:40,120
Please rise and speak.

558
00:27:40,120 --> 00:27:41,580
Thank you, Your Highness.

559
00:27:42,760 --> 00:27:44,360
Your Highness, we are

560
00:27:44,400 --> 00:27:46,200
former subordinates
of the Marquis of Jing'an.

561
00:27:46,200 --> 00:27:47,400
When Guo Bingmao took office,

562
00:27:47,400 --> 00:27:50,040
he used the excuse of military
training to eliminate his enemies.

563
00:27:50,040 --> 00:27:51,760
Those who opposed him in the past

564
00:27:51,760 --> 00:27:53,450
have all been beaten to death.

